@prev "Main"
@{u}001:@{uu}

   You enter Sepulchre Wood - so called because of all the brave young
   adventurers just like yourself who have, in one way or another, been 
   laid to rest within it's boundaries. It is greatly advised that a map
   is made of Sepulchre Wood highlighting clearings and markings of 
   importance.  All clearings are numbered for your reference and all 
   distances are multiples of five (unless otherwise stated) for ease
   of mapping.  Your mission will become apparent when you find the wizard
   Haddagon who has been encarcerated within the forest by the evil
   necromancer Zephilis.   Zephilis' superior magic keeps Haddagon locked
   up and doomed to a life of being fed by goblins.
    Sword sheathed comfortably by your side you walk north into
   Sepulchre Wood.
            @{" 346 " link "346" 0}   
@endnode

